.TH "change_xattr" 9 "change_xattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
change_xattr \- change an extended attribute.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" change_xattr
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct inode *host "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "const void *value "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "host" 12
host inode
.IP "inode" 12
extended attribute inode
.IP "value" 12
extended attribute value
.IP "size" 12
size of extended attribute value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function changes the value of extended attribute \fIinode\fP with new
data from \fIvalue\fP. Returns zero in case of success and a negative error code
in case of failure.
